The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Bolan Pir, the taxi driver who was assaulted on Ripon Street on July 5, died at National Medical College and Hospital on Monday. Mohammad Kamrujjaman, 30, has been arrested in connection with the assault. Citu has called a 12-hour taxi strike from 6am on Tuesday to protest the assault.   he three key unions of taxi owners  Bengal Taxi Association, Calcutta Taxi Association and Progressive Taximens Association  said they would not join the strike.  ransport department officials and a section of operators said taxi services on Tuesday would remain largely unaffected as only those drivers and mechanics who were loyal to Citu would stay away from work. Citu sources said they would not force any taxi to stay off the road. Of the 42,000-odd taxis in the city, around 33,000 ply on a normal day.    A 14-year-old boy was arrested in Chetla on Monday for allegedly trying to molest a 10-year-old pavement dweller two days ago. The girl complained that the boy had tried to molest her around Saturday midnight. Other pavement dwellers caught the boy as the girl raised an alarm, said an officer of Alipore police station.    Mohammad Rizwan and Amir Hamza were arrested at a Kidderpore market on Monday with 2 kg charas, worth Rs 2 lakh, on them.    Saheb Kapasi, 18, and Subir Chakrabarty, 19, were arrested on Monday for allegedly snatching a gold chain from a woman near a temple in Cossipore. Two youths snatched a gold chain from Swapna Ghoshal around 7pm on July 16 and ran away, said a police officer. Witnesses helped police arrest the duo.                                                                                                                                               
